{"title_page": "Tom Dodson", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic sailor from New Zealand}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Tom Dodson<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" />\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| native_name    = \n| birth_name     =  \n| fullname       = Thomas Ward Dodson \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{NZL}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1957|5|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Hastings, New Zealand]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.83|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = \n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 27 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Thomas Ward Dodson''' (born 17 May 1957) is a sailor from [[Hastings, New Zealand]], who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1984 Summer Olympics]] in [[Los Angeles]], [[United States]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]].<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" /> With crew members [[Simon Daubney]] and [[Aran Hansen]] they took the 11th place.<ref name=\"OS1984\" /> Dodson took also part in the [[Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Busan]], [[South Korea]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]]. With same crew members then they took the 7th place.<ref name=\"OS1988\" />\n{{Footer New Zealand Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{1984 New Zealand Olympic team}}\n{{1988 New Zealand Olympic team}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/do/tom-dodson-1.html\n                                  |title      = Tom Dodson Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n 