{"title_page": "MasterChef (American season 10)", "text_new": "{{short description|American competitive reality TV series}}\n{{Infobox television season\n |season_number= 10\n |bgcolour     = \n |image        = \n |caption      = \n |country      = United States\n |num_episodes = 25\n\n |network      = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n |first_aired  = {{Start date|2019|5|29}}\n |last_aired   = {{End date|2019|9|18}} \n |prev_season  = [[MasterChef (American season 9)|Season 9]]\n |next_season  = \n |episode_list = \n|}}\n\n'''Season 10''' of the American competitive [[reality television|reality TV]] series '''''[[MasterChef (American TV series)|MasterChef]]''''' premiered on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] on May 29, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/03/27/fox-announces-summer-premiere-dates-205310/20190327fox02/|title=FOX Announces Summer Premiere Dates|website=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=March 27, 2019|access-date=May 25, 2019}}</ref> [[Gordon Ramsay]], [[Aar\u00f3n Sanchez]], and [[Joe Bastianich]] all returned as judges.\n\nDorian Hunter was announced as the winner, with Sarah Faherty as the runner-up.\n\n==Top 20==\nExcept where otherwise cited, source for names, hometowns and occupations:<ref name=official-press-release-contestants>{{cite press release|url=https://www.foxflash.com/shows/masterchef/releases/view/the-milestone-10th-season-of-masterchef-kicks-off-with-another-crop-of-talented-home-cooks|title=The Milestone 10th Season of 'MasterChef' Kicks Off with Another Crop of Talented Home Cooks|publisher=[[Fox Broadcasting]]|date= May 21, 2019|accessdate= May 30, 2019}}</ref> Ages and nicknames as given on air.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#C1D8FF;\"\n! style=\"width:18%;\" |Contestant\n! style=\"width:4%;\"  |Age\n! style=\"width:20%;\" |Hometown\n! style=\"width:20%;\" |Occupation\n! style=\"width:16%;\" class=\"unsortable\" |Status\n|-\n| Dorian Hunter\n| 45\n|[[Cartersville, Georgia]]\n| Creeler\n| style=\"background:green;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Winner September 18</span>\n|-\n| Sarah Faherty\n| 31\n|[[San Diego, California]]\n| Former Army Interrogator\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;\" rowspan=\"1\"|{{nowrap|Runner-up September 18}}\n|-\n| Nick DiGiovanni\n| 22\n|[[Barrington, Rhode Island]]\n| College Student\n|style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text'align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated September 18\n|-\n| Noah Sims\n| 32\n|[[Epworth, Georgia]]\n| Septic Service Technician\n|style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text'align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated September 11\n|-\n| Shari Mukherjee\n| 34\n|[[Rochester, Minnesota]]\n| Stay-at-Home Mom\n|style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text'align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" |Eliminated September 4\n|-\n| Subha Ramiah\n| 54\n|[[West Nyack, New York]]\n| R&D Director\n|-\n| Micah Yaroch\n| 19\n|[[Grand Rapids, Michigan]]\n| Kitchen Porter\n|style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text'align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated August 28\n|-\n| Brielle \"Bri\" Baker<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bernardini |first1=Gabrielle |title=Meet Season 10 'MasterChef' Finalist Bri Baker, Aka the \"Plating Queen\" |url=https://www.distractify.com/p/brielle-baker-masterchef |website=Distractify.com |accessdate=July 11, 2019 |date=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n| 24\n| [[Dallas, Texas]]\n| Cocktail Server\n| style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text'align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated August 21\n|-\n| Jamie Hough\n| 42\n|[[Pawleys Island, South Carolina]]\n| Fisherman\n| style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated August 15\n|-\n| Fred Chang\n| 24\n|[[Redondo Beach, California]]\n| Revenue Analyst\n| style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated August 8\n|-\n| Wuta Onda\n| 30\n|[[Bronx, New York]]\n| English Teacher\n| style=\"background:#f4c4b8; text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |Eliminated August 1\n|-\n| Renee Rice\n| 33\n|[[Ada, Oklahoma]]\n| Receptio