irs.\n* '''Immune:''' Bri Baker, Evan Tesiny, Fred Chang, Keturah King, Liz Linn, Nick DiGiovanni, Noah Sims and Sam Haaz\n| LineColor       = #64DB88\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = The Blind Chicken Show\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|6|20}}\n| Viewers         = 2.84<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-june-20-2019/|title='Holey Moley,' 'MasterChef,' all others unchanged: Thursday final ratings|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|work=TV by the Numbers|date=June 21, 2019|accessdate=June 21, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = \n*'''Pressure Test Part 1:''' For the first part of the pressure test, the Red Team and Subha had five minutes to perfectly cut a whole chicken. Dorian, Jamie and Michael had the best attempts and they were deemed safe.\n*'''Immune:''' Dorian Hunter, Jamie Hough and Michael Silverstein\n*'''Pressure Test Part 2:''' The remaining home cooks had 45 minutes to cook a chicken dish with the chicken they just cut. Wuta, Renee, and Kimberly were in the bottom three.\n*'''Bottom three:''' Kimberly White, Renee Rice and Wuta Onda\n*Kimberly was eliminated.\n*'''Eliminated:''' Kimberly White\n| LineColor       = #64DB88\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| Title           = Hot & Spicy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|6|26}}\n| Viewers         = 2.61<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-june-26-2019/|title=Democratic Debate adjusts up, 'The Amazing Race' adjusts down: Wednesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=June 27, 2019|accessdate=June 27, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = \n*'''Mystery Box Challenge:''' [[Alessandra Ambrosio]] joined the judges to introduce the challenge. The contestants had one hour to cook a dish featuring at least one of Latin American cuisine's staple proteins. After thirty minutes of cooking time, the judges also asked them to make a [[ceviche]] t